* INSTALL POSTGRES (STEP 1)

    Download the interactive Postgres Database Installer from here :
        https://www.enterprisedb.com/downloads/postgres-postgresql-downloads

    Follow the instructions in the installer.


* CREATE A NEW USER  (STEP 2)

    Step 1) Open the SQL Shell

    Step 2) Press enter five times to connect to the DB

    Step 3) Create a new postgres user called npm with password 'npm' using the following command:

                create user npm with password 'npm';


* CREATE DATABASE IN Postgres  (STEP 3)

    Step 1) Open the SQL Shell

    Step 2) Press enter five times to connect to the DB

    Step 3) Enter the command

        CREATE DATABASE np_manager;

    Step 4) Enter command \l to get a list of all databases

    Step 5) To connect to a Database use the command

        \c np_manager



* GRANT PRIVILEGES (STEP 4):

    Grant the user 'npm' privileges to the database 'np_manager' using the following command:

        grant all privileges on database np_manager to npm;



* IMPORT THE DATABASE USING THE 'IMPORT' COMMAND MENTIONED BELOW (STEP 5):


------------------------------------------------------------ DUMP AND RESTORE COMMANDS ----------------------------------------------------------

* Export/Dump the np_manager Database:

    Use the following command to export/dump the current database into np_manager.sql file. The file will be created in the directory where this command is executed (This saves the current snapshot of the DB into an sql file):

        pg_dump -U postgres -h localhost -p 5432 --clean --file=np_manager.sql np_manager


* Import/Restore the np_manager Database:

    Use the following command using the np_manager.sql file located in the resources folder. Replace the [path/to/] with actual path to the np_manager.sql file in your local machine

        psql -U postgres -h localhost -p 5432 np_manager < [path/to/]np_manager.sql